# Responsive UI — mobile, tablet, desktop

All UI must be usable at every breakpoint. Design **mobile-first**: start with the smallest
viewport and progressively enhance for tablet (≥ 768 px) and desktop (≥ 1280 px).

## Breakpoints

Use these named breakpoints consistently (Tailwind defaults align with them):

| Name    | Min width | Tailwind prefix |
|---------|-----------|-----------------|
| mobile  | 0 px      | (base)          |
| tablet  | 768 px    | `md:`           |
| desktop | 1280 px   | `xl:`           |

## Layout rules

- **Fluid by default.** Use `w-full`, `max-w-*`, `min-w-0`, and relative units (`%`, `rem`,
  `ch`) — never fixed pixel widths on containers.
- **Flex / Grid, not absolute positioning** for layout; let content reflow naturally.
- **Touch targets ≥ 44 × 44 px** (buttons, links, interactive elements).
- **No horizontal overflow** — test with `overflow-x: hidden` on `<body>`.
- Stack single-column on mobile → multi-column on `md:` and wider.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD: fixed-width sidebar, breaks on mobile
<div className="flex">
  <aside className="w-64">…</aside>
  <main>…</main>
</div>

// ✅ GOOD: hidden on mobile, visible sidebar on tablet+
<div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row">
  <aside className="hidden md:block md:w-64 shrink-0">…</aside>
  <main className="flex-1 min-w-0 p-4">…</main>
</div>
```

## Typography & spacing

- Base font size ≥ 16 px; use `text-base` (never below `text-sm` for body copy).
- Scale spacing with Tailwind spacing tokens; avoid hardcoded `px` values in `className`.

## Navigation

- Collapse top-nav into a hamburger / bottom-bar on mobile (`< md:`).
- Modals and drawers must be full-screen or near-full-screen on mobile.

## Images & media

- Always set explicit `width` + `height` on `<img>` to prevent layout shift.
- Use `object-cover` / `object-contain`; never let images overflow their container.

## Testing checklist (required before marking done)

- [ ] Renders without horizontal scroll at 375 px, 768 px, and 1280 px viewports.
- [ ] Touch targets meet the 44 × 44 px minimum.
- [ ] Playwright / Vitest snapshot includes at least one mobile-width assertion.
- [ ] No hardcoded pixel widths on layout containers.
